    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>.claude/patterns/ai/streaming-endpoints.md — SSE event types from BFF: token, done, error, typing_start, typing_end</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The existing `useSseStream` hook performs POST-based SSE (not EventSource, since EventSource only supports GET). R1 implemented the basic streaming plumbing but did not add typing indicators or per-token rendering — messages appeared all at once. R2 requires copilot-quality streaming UX: animated typing indicator before first token, then smooth character-by-character accumulation.

      The BFF SSE endpoint (task R2-010) emits these event types: `typing_start` (AI is processing, show indicator), `token` (append to accumulator), `typing_end` (indicator off), `done` (streaming complete, finalize message), `error` (show error state). The frontend hook must handle all of these.

      SprkChat.tsx manages the `messages` state array. During streaming, an in-progress assistant message should appear in the messages list with an `isStreaming: true` flag, accumulating tokens. On `done`, the message is finalized.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on R2-004 (shared library baseline) and R2-006 (Phase 1 deploy for any foundation changes). Can run in parallel with R2-030, R2-032, R2-033. Task R2-033 (plan preview streaming) depends on the patterns established here. Task R2-050 (SSE integration) depends on this task.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read useSseStream.ts to understand the current POST-based SSE implementation, event handling, and return shape</step>
    <step order="1">Read SprkChat.tsx message state management — understand how messages are added and updated in the messages array</step>
    <step order="2">Read streaming-endpoints.md pattern to understand all SSE event types the BFF emits and their payloads</step>
    <step order="3">Enhance useSseStream to handle typing_start event: set isTyping=true state, expose via hook return</step>
    <step order="4">Enhance useSseStream to handle token events: accumulate token text into streamingContent string, trigger React state update per token for real-time rendering</step>
    <step order="5">Enhance useSseStream to handle typing_end and done events: finalize the accumulated message, clear isTyping and streamingContent</step>
    <step order="6">Add AbortController support to useSseStream: expose a cancel() function; call abort() on the AbortController signal to terminate the fetch stream; clean up on component unmount</step>
    <step order="7">Create a TypingIndicator component with animated dots using Fluent v9 motion tokens — three dots with staggered fade/scale animation</step>
    <step order="8">Update SprkChat.tsx to show TypingIndicator when useSseStream returns isTyping=true</step>
    <step order="9">Update SprkChat.tsx to render the in-progress streaming message with accumulated tokens as a special message bubble (isStreaming flag) that updates without re-mounting</step>
    <step order="10">Add a cancel button (Fluent v9 Button) visible during streaming — calls the cancel() function from useSseStream</step>
    <step order="11">Handle error events: display an error message in the chat and clear streaming state cleanly</step>
    <step order="12">Run TypeScript compilation: cd src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components &amp;&amp; npx tsc --noEmit — verify 0 errors</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-031 status to completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>npm</tool>
    <tool>git</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">useSseStream.ts — enhanced hook with typing_start/token/done/error event handling, AbortController cancellation, isTyping and streamingContent states</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">TypingIndicator.tsx — animated three-dot indicator component using Fluent v9 motion tokens</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">SprkChat.tsx — updated to show TypingIndicator, render streaming message bubble, expose cancel button</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">After sending a message, typing indicator (animated dots) appears immediately — visible before first token arrives</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Token-by-token text appears progressively in the assistant message bubble — no flicker or full re-render on each token</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Cancel button appears during streaming; clicking it aborts the SSE connection and clears in-progress message</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SSE error events result in an error message in chat — component does not crash</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">On component unmount, the AbortController aborts any active stream — no memory leaks</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TypeScript compilation passes with 0 errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Typing indicator uses Fluent v9 motion tokens — no hard-coded animation timing values</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
